It’s National infertility Awareness Week and honestly I wasn’t sure how I wanted to share our fertility journey.

After 5 years of trying, 2 failed ivf transfers, and 1 surgery, we are preparing to welcome our baby girl. If you told me a year ago that this journey would have been what it was I wouldn’t have believed you.  I wouldn’t have believed that my faith, my relationships, and even my belief would be tested. 

We are here now and I couldn’t have asked for a better journey. 

My doctors @cnyfertility were amazing as well as the staff. 
@verdialesmd 

1 in 6 people (not just women) struggle with infertility. That’s a lot of people for the subject to be so taboo. 

Thanks to some of my ivf warriors who were so necessary for my personal journey. @deandrabrownglobal @iamerickaj @narissaroperart @shennamari. I needed you ladies more than I could ever express. And I’m here for anyone else walking this road. 

Grateful is an understatement and 
God is so faithful to his promises 🙌🏾🙌🏾
“For this child we prayed”
#nationalinfertilityawarenessweek 

Tap the link in my bio the full video part 1 of our journey!

1 retrieval
2 transfers and 
1 surgery later… 
Grateful is an understatement!!
God did it!!! 
Click the link in my bio to watch the full video on YouTube. 

#ivfjourney #ivf #cnyfertility #fertilitytreatment #newyork #atlanta #ivfsuccess #ivfwarrior #tubalremoval
